         <abstract id="aspace_204a9b44b904eb879786e8575332bad8">The collection is comprised of a sampling of the work of two architects, Frank Lupo and Daniel Rowen, as well as their work together in partnership as the architecture firm New York Architects.  Four major projects are represented through drawings, photographs, and job files; four additional projects are documented by sketches and presentation drawings.  Lupo and Rowen, both alumni of the Yale School of Architecture, were protégés of the architect Charles Gwathmey, and formed their own partnership in 1984.  Their work was largely concentrated in New York City and environs.</abstract>
         <langmaterial id="aspace_09771ae06a860607f2d64fa2b7d0dd24">
